This file contains a small wordlist for people who, like me, are not
that familiar with the terminology of MS Word.

Major features
--------------

PAP - PAragraph Properties
CHP - CHaracter Properties
TAP - TAble Properties(?)

Minor features
--------------

BRC - BoRder Code (found inside a PAP)
      Used to describe paragraph borders.
DCS - Drop Cap Style (found inside a PAP)
      Used to describe drop caps properties of a paragraph.
JC  - Justification Code (found inside a PAP)
      Used for paragraph alignment.
LSPD - Line SPacing Descriptor (found inside a PAP)
TBD - TaB Descriptor (found inside a PAP)
      Used for tab stops.

